Today, I had the privilege of joining our Cyber Security cohort on a site visit to Cox Enterprises. It was an inspiring experience, as we were hosted by Hadji Hicks and Gabriel Egwu, both of whom are graduates of the same Cyber Security cohort we’re currently in. Hearing their success stories and experiences at Cox was both motivating and eye-opening.

Key Takeaways from the Visit:
Learning from Alumni: Hadji and Gabriel shared their journeys—how they transitioned from this program into professional cybersecurity roles. Their insights gave me a real sense of what’s possible after completing the program.

Workplace Exposure: Seeing the Cox Enterprises environment helped me visualize myself in a cybersecurity role within a large organization. It made the career path feel more tangible and achievable.

Professional Networking: Meeting cybersecurity professionals who are actively advancing their careers was a great opportunity to build connections and learn from their experiences.

This visit reinforced the importance of mentorship, networking, and hands-on experience in building a successful cybersecurity career. It was inspiring to see former students thriving in the industry, and I left feeling energized and more determined to push forward in my own journey.
